  "body": "Hi there,\r\n\r\nplease note that this is an issue tracker reserved for bug reports and feature requests.\r\n\r\nFor general questions please use the gitter channel or the Ethereum stack exchange at https://ethereum.stackexchange.com.\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: ` 1.7.3-stable-4bb3c89d`\r\nOS & Version: `Linux`\r\n\r\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nContractName is:  BNB\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nquery name err:no contract code at given address\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n*Build a geth node with command:\r\ngeth --datadir ~/.ethash --rpcport 8545 --rpc --rpcapi \"web3,eth,net,personal\" --rpcaddr 0.0.0.0 --syncmode \"full\"\r\n* waiting this node sync all exists blocks done\r\n\r\n*run this main.go\r\n```\r\npackage main\r\n\r\nimport (\r\n    \"github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/ethclient\"\r\n    \"github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/common\"\r\n    \"./src/bcdn\"\r\n    \"fmt\"\r\n    \"log\"\r\n)\r\n\r\nvar contractAddress = \"0xB8c77482e45F1F44dE1745F52C74426C631bDD52\"\r\n\r\nfunc main() {\r\n    // Create an IPC based RPC connection to a remote node and instantiate a contract binding\r\n\r\n    nodeAddr := \"http://192.168.3.198:8545\"\r\n    // nodeAddr := \"https://mainnet.infura.io/\" + \"myApiKey\"\r\n    conn, err := ethclient.Dial(nodeAddr)\r\n\tif err != nil {\r\n        log.Fatalf(\"Failed to connect to the Ethereum client: %v\", err)\r\n    }\r\n    token, err := bcdn.NewBlockcdn(common.HexToAddress(contractAddress), conn)\r\n    if err != nil {\r\n        log.Fatalf(\"Failed to instantiate a Token contract: %v\", err)\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    contractName, err := token.Name(nil)\r\n    if err != nil {\r\n        log.Fatalf(\"query name err:%v\", err)\r\n    }\r\n    fmt.Printf(\"ContractName is: %s\\n\", contractName)\r\n\treturn\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\nI can get the contract name through my infura api-key but it doesn't work with the local node, where did I wrong?\r\n",
